---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Maps" description="Public maps of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts</p>
    <h1>Maps</h1>
    <p class="lede">Maps help readers understand place, relation, and route inside Vaelinya.</p>
    <p>A map can show boundary, nearness, distance, and how one place affects another. It helps the world feel travelled rather than abstract.</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>↔</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">First map layer</p>
        <h2>Reader orientation</h2>
        <p>The first map is a simple reading map: Lina, the Rim, the Rimaeri, and the Warm Remembering. It explains where to begin without requiring a full atlas.</p>
        <a class="visual-callout-link" href="/artefacts/maps/reader-orientation/">Open the reader orientation map</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Map access rule</p>
      <h2>Maps must also be understandable as text</h2>
      <p>Vaelinya maps may become illustrated later, but every important map must have a readable route description so blind, partially sighted, and text-only readers can still follow the world.</p>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/world/the-rim/">Places of the world</a>
      <a href="/artefacts/story-objects/">Story objects</a>
      <a href="/read/lina/">Read Lina</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
